<section id="overview">
      <h2>Year Overview</h2>
      <p>The Monkey (<span class="chinese-char">猴</span>) occupies the Earthly Branch <strong>Shen (申)</strong>, carrying Yang Metal energy with hidden Water and Earth. In the 2026 Fire Horse year, the Monkey faces the <strong>overcoming cycle</strong> — Fire melts Metal, creating pressure on the Monkey's core nature.</p>
      <p>This relationship is best understood through the <strong>metaphor of the forge</strong>. Raw metal ore enters the fire and emerges as something more refined — a blade, a tool, a work of art. The year's challenges are not destructive but transformative. The Monkey's quick intelligence, problem-solving ability, and talent for improvisation are tested and strengthened.</p>
      <p>The Monkey also carries hidden Earth energy (戊 Wu within Shen), which receives support from the Fire year through the generating cycle. This means the Monkey's practical, grounded side benefits even while the Metal aspect faces pressure. The Monkey who leans into practical skills and grounded decision-making navigates 2026 with greater ease than one who relies solely on cleverness.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="fire-controls-metal">
      <h2>Fire Controls Metal — The Overcoming Cycle (火剋金)</h2>
      <div class="callout-box callout-box--jade">
        <div class="callout-icon">⚒️</div>
        <div class="callout-content">
          <h3>The Refining Relationship</h3>
          <p>The Monkey belongs to <strong>Yang Metal</strong> (庚金) — the axe, the sword, the raw ore. In the five-phase overcoming cycle, <strong>Fire controls Metal</strong>: the 2026 Fire Horse year exerts pressure on the Monkey's core element. Fire melts metal, reshapes it, refines it. This is a year of <em>transformation under pressure</em>.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p>The Fire-Metal dynamic is not simply adversarial. In traditional metallurgy, fire is essential for transforming raw ore into useful tools and beautiful objects. The <em>Kaogong Ji</em> (考工記, Warring States period) describes six stages of metal smelting — each requiring precise fire control. The Monkey in 2026 undergoes a similar process: uncomfortable but ultimately refining.</p>
      <p>What Fire-controls-Metal means for Monkey-born people:</p>
      <ul class="feature-list">
        <li><strong>Pressure creates diamonds</strong> — external challenges force the Monkey to develop new skills, discard inefficient habits, and emerge sharper</li>
        <li><strong>Authority figures</strong> — Fire's controlling energy may manifest through demanding bosses, regulatory requirements, or competitive rivals; respond with strategy, not rebellion</li>
        <li><strong>Respiratory and skin health</strong> — Metal governs the lungs and skin in Chinese medicine; Fire's control may trigger respiratory issues or skin sensitivity; preventive care is wise</li>
        <li><strong>Water as mediator</strong> — Water controls Fire and generates Metal; the Rat (San He ally) and Water-element activities provide crucial relief and support</li>
      </ul>
      <p><strong>Strategic advantage:</strong> The Monkey's intelligence and adaptability are its greatest assets under pressure. While other Metal signs might rigidly resist Fire's forge, the Monkey <em>adapts</em> — bending rather than breaking. Channel Fire's energy into self-improvement projects, certifications, and skill development rather than fighting it.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="career">
      <h2>Career &amp; Finance</h2>
      <p>Career challenges centre on <strong>authority and structure</strong>. Fire's energy can melt the Monkey's carefully constructed plans and systems, requiring rapid adaptation. Workplace politics may be more intense than usual, with power dynamics shifting unpredictably. The Monkey's ability to read situations and pivot quickly is the key survival skill.</p>
      <p><strong>Finance</strong> requires defensive management. Metal represents wealth accumulation, and Fire's pressure means existing savings or investments may face losses. Diversification, conservative positioning, and avoiding speculative ventures protect the Monkey's resources. The second half of the year (after the summer Fire peak) is more favourable for financial recovery.</p>
      <p><strong>Best sectors:</strong> Technology, engineering, innovation, problem-solving roles, consulting, and any field where adaptability is valued more than rigid expertise. The Monkey's ability to learn fast and pivot is a competitive advantage during chaotic times.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="love">
      <h2>Love &amp; Relationships</h2>
      <p>Romantic relationships in 2026 require <strong>patience and emotional maturity</strong>. Fire's controlling energy on Metal can make the Monkey feel constrained or misunderstood in partnerships. The tendency to use humour as deflection may frustrate partners who seek deeper emotional engagement.</p>
      <p><strong>Single Monkeys</strong> attract attention through demonstrated competence and wit, but lasting connections require showing vulnerability — difficult under Fire's pressure. The Dragon month (April) and Rat month (December) are most favourable for meaningful romantic encounters, as San He allies provide emotional safety.</p>
      <p><strong>The Snake</strong> — the Monkey's Liu He secret friend — is also navigating strong Fire energy in 2026. These two signs can provide mutual support and understanding through shared experience of the year's intensity.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="health">
      <h2>Health &amp; Wellness</h2>
      <p>Fire overcoming Metal manifests in <strong>respiratory and skin conditions</strong> — the organs and tissues governed by Metal in Chinese medicine. The lungs, large intestine, and skin are vulnerable. Avoid smoky environments, manage allergies proactively, and maintain good skincare routines.</p>
      <p><strong>Mental health</strong> benefits from the Monkey's natural resilience, but cumulative stress can build. Creative outlets, social connection (especially with trusted allies), and physical activity help discharge tension. Competitive sports provide a healthy channel for the Monkey's Fire-aggravated intensity.</p>
      <p><strong>Breathing exercises</strong> and qigong are particularly beneficial, directly supporting the lung energy that is under pressure. Swimming combines water's cooling influence with cardiovascular fitness.</p>
    </section>

